{
  "message": "fuzz(openfs-journal-replay): 18 structured seeds across SeedCase \u00d7 replay-mode \u00d7 extras\n\nfuzz_openfs_journal_replay drives `OpenFs::from_device` through every\njournal flavor (InternalJournal, FastCommit, ExternalJournalClean,\nExternalJournalDirty, WalOnly) with optional WAL/external-journal\nattach toggles, an ORPHAN_FS state bool, and pick_options inputs.\nExisting 4 ad-hoc seeds covered only the default of each flavor with\nno replay-mode toggle and no orphan flag.\n\nAdds 18 seeds spanning the relevant slices of the input phase space:\n\n  Replay-mode toggles per SeedCase:\n  * InternalJournal \u00d7 Apply / SimulateOverlay / Skip\n  * FastCommit \u00d7 default + with WAL + with external\n  * ExternalJournalClean default + orphan-without-path\n  * ExternalJournalDirty default + Skip mode\n  * WalOnly default + Apply-with-path + orphan + Skip\n\n  Optional-attach combinations:\n  * InternalJournal + add_wal=1 (provide_wal_path=1)\n  * InternalJournal + attach_external (clean & dirty)\n  * FastCommit + add_wal=1 + orphan_flag=1\n  * FastCommit + attach_external + Skip mode\n\n  ORPHAN_FS state covered for InternalJournal, FastCommit,\n  ExternalJournalClean, and WalOnly.\n\n  External-path provision:\n  * ExternalJournalClean + orphan but provide_external_path=0\n    (drives the \"no path supplied for external\" branch)\n\nAll 22 corpus inputs load cleanly with `-runs=0`; coverage rises to\n2 169 PCs / 3 126 features.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
